mdElement.text: These projects use massively the maven pluginEachEach xxx-spec project contains a UML model.The xxx-api, xxx-impl projects are generated using the from-spec of language modules.

A Generic Expression LanguageThe implementation is supposed to be used in place of JSR 341 expression languageThe specification is based on Object Constraint Language specificationhttp://www.omg.org/spec/OCL/2.4/PDF
An execution language defined as a subset of Action Language for Foundational UML (Alf) specificationhttp://www.omg.org/spec/ALF/1.1xlang stand for eXecution LANGuage
Classes in this package read OCL (Gel) specifications and build various sets of xlang statements

The purpose of the whole project is to run an mda process.The core of the project is the ete-lib subproject.This project defines a process through pipelines of actions. Each action takes an eventual model on entry and returns a model.This diagram shows the very first layer : these packages enable embedding mda processes into a standard Java processEach package is materialized as a (sub)project
Implementation of dynamic versions of Visitor and AbstractFactory design patternsActually, this is not a subproject of ete but a standalone project.
Contains an adapter for the JSR 341 language
The ete-maven-plugin facilitates the use of the library through a maven process.
